The paper focuses on modelling sentence pairs using a combination of tree-structured recursive neural networks and sequential recurrent neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category of computer science, which is cs.CL. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel way to incorporate attention into the tree topology, which could be of interest to researchers working on machine learning models for natural language understanding and generation. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.NE (neural networks), and cs.CV (computer vision), which are all relevant to the development of NLP models.
